[1]
Date: Thu 4 Feb 2010
From: Hugh Baker <drhugh@sympatico.ca> [edited]


Based on my brief visits to Manhattan, I wonder whether feral cats
might be cycling the raccoon strain back into the raccoon population.
In cats, the raccoon strain is known to be inapparent to the casual
observer.

If authorities are vaccine baiting with the baits we use in Canada for
raccoons, cats would be unlikely to take the bait, which has a
marshmallow-based attractant.

--
HJ Baker, BSc, DVM
Etobicoke, Ontario
Canada
<drhugh@sympatico.ca>

