[What an excellent discussion! ProMED-mail is grateful and
appreciative to Dr Baker, Mr Clifton, and Mr Kortis.

And what a perfect opportunity to remind pet owners to vaccinate their
pets. It may save their lives and even yours. Whether you have a dog,
or a cat, or some other pet, vaccination against rabies is critical
for their protection and is cheap insurance to protect your life.

Dr Baker brought up an interesting point regarding oral rabies bait.
One of the keys to successful oral rabies vaccination bait is
acceptance by the target species. Several flavors of bait exist
including fish, poultry, beef, cheese, and a mixture of flavors. While
I am not sure how the marshmallow bait came about, I know it was used
as a target for foxes, and the spillover was raccoon acceptance of the
bait.

While flavor is important in attracting the desired target, there is
also an odor effect on the individuals putting out the baits. Baits
are generally put out from an airplane with a hopper of sorts that
must be loaded with the bait. Imagine how fish bait smells on a hot
summer day in a plane! Of course the sweet smell of marshmallow after
a few hours in a plane may not be any more desirable, I am sure. Bait
flavors are selected on the basis of the desired target, not on the
comfort of the individuals loading the hopper of the plane. - Mod.TG]

[Map of New York City boroughs
<http://www.ecampmany.com/NY/nyc-boroughs-map.jpg>
- Mod:JW]
